Purpose:
Create a minimal base game and then mods to extend it. Each step should be focused in part on creating a real game but also as a tutorial for future modders.


The Pitch:
Vanguard University is an urban fantasy life-simulator where your greatest academic tool is your own physical identity. As a student at a college "awake" to the supernatural, you navigate the daily pressures of grades, finances, and relationships by using mana-fueled rituals to modularly transform your body. Using a deep, parts-based configuration system, you can swap limbs, senses, and frames to gain vital stat boosts for jobs or social encounters—but every transformation is a commitment. Whether you’re sacrificing logic for the strength of a primal form to pay your tuition, or trading human normalcy for fae intuition to ace an exam, you must strategically balance your magical "loadout" against the social and academic consequences of no longer being entirely human.

